cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper discusses the use of neural networks for deep learning and connectionist viewpoints, which are typically associated with the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on Bayesian inference and Boltzmann machines suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the mention of variational inference and the potential applications to image recognition suggest a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
